.TH LSPORT 1 "January 2026" "lsport 0.2.10" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lsport \- TUI for managing local and remote ports via SSH
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lsport
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lsport
is a fast, interactive terminal user interface for managing ports on local
and remote machines via SSH. It allows you to quickly identify which process
is using a port and kill it with a single keystroke.
.PP
Features include live port monitoring with real-time updates, TCP and UDP
support, remote server monitoring via SSH, Vim-style navigation, process
termination, regex filtering, and a k9s-inspired dark theme UI.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-H ", " \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Remote host to monitor. Format: \fIuser@host:port\fR or \fIuser@host\fR or \fIhost\fR.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-identity " " \fIPATH\fR
Path to SSH private key. If not specified, uses ssh-agent or default keys
(~/.ssh/id_ed25519, ~/.ssh/id_rsa, ~/.ssh/id_ecdsa).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-scan\-interval " " \fISECS\fR
Scan interval in seconds. Default is 2.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.BR \(ua " / " k
Move selection up.
.TP
.BR \(da " / " j
Move selection down.
.TP
.B PgUp
Move up 10 rows.
.TP
.B PgDn
Move down 10 rows.
.TP
.B Home
Go to first entry.
.TP
.B End
Go to last entry.
.SS Actions
.TP
.B Enter
Kill selected process.
.TP
.B /
Enter filter mode (supports regex).
.TP
.B ?
Toggle help popup.
.TP
.B Esc
Clear filter or close help.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SS Sorting (K9s-style)
.TP
.BR Shift+P " / " 1
Sort by Port.
.TP
.BR Shift+O " / " 2
Sort by Protocol.
.TP
.BR Shift+I " / " 3
Sort by PID.
.TP
.BR Shift+N " / " 4
Sort by Name.
.TP
.BR Shift+C " / " 5
Sort by CPU %.
.TP
.BR Shift+M " / " 6
Sort by Memory.
.PP
Press the same key again to toggle ascending/descending order.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Monitor localhost:
.B lsport
.TP
Monitor with sudo (needed for killing system processes):
.B sudo lsport
.TP
Monitor a remote server via SSH:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com
.TP
Remote server with custom SSH port:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com:2222
.TP
Use a specific SSH key:
.B lsport \-\-host user@example.com \-i ~/.ssh/my_key
.TP
Custom scan interval (5 seconds):
.B lsport \-s 5
.SH SSH AUTHENTICATION
For remote monitoring, authentication is attempted in this order:
.IP 1. 4
Specified key (\fB\-i\fR flag)
.IP 2. 4
SSH agent (if running)
.IP 3. 4
Default keys: ~/.ssh/id_ed25519, ~/.ssh/id_rsa, ~/.ssh/id_ecdsa
.SH FILTERING
Press \fB/\fR to enter filter mode. Filters support:
.IP \(bu 4
Simple text: \fBnode\fR matches any entry containing "node"
.IP \(bu 4
Regex patterns: \fB^80[0-9]{2}$\fR matches ports 8000-8099
.IP \(bu 4
All filters are case-insensitive
